    <div class="pb-5">
        Lutendi Systems Inc. (“Lutendi Systems”, “us”, “we”, “our”), is committed to protecting your privacy. We own and operate the website located at [www.lutendi.com] and [app.lutendi.com] (“Website”). Lutendi Systems is a service that reports rental payments on behalf of landlords to Equifax, a credit bureau. By reporting your rental payment history, you have the opportunity to build and maintain a positive credit history. Lutendi uses bank level (AES-256) encryption standards to ensure that your data is secure from end-to-end. Lutendi Systems provides a streamlined integration designed to transform the rental landscape. Every month, your rental payments are automatically updated on your Equifax credit report.
    </div>
    <div class="pb-5">
        This privacy policy (“Privacy Policy”) describes how we collect, store, use, and distribute your information, including personally identifiable information about an individual (“Personal Information”), via the Services. Please read the following carefully to understand our practices regarding Personal Information of users who access and browse the Website or use the Platform (“User”, “you”, “your”). 
    </div>
    <div class="pb-5">
        We may change this Privacy Policy from time to time at our sole discretion. Lutendi Systems Inc.  may require you to provide consent to the updated Privacy Policy before further use of the Services is permitted.
    </div>
    <div class="pb-5">
        <span class="font-bold">1. Consent. </span>By using the Platform, you consent to the collection, use and disclosure of your Personal Information as described in this Privacy Policy. Except as set forth in this Privacy Policy, your Personal Information will not be collected, stored, used, or disclosed for any other purpose without your consent.
    </div>
    <div class="pb-5">
        <span class="font-bold">2. Information We Collect When You Use the Services. </span>
        <br>
        <div class="pl-10">
            <span class="font-bold">a. Personal Information via the Platform. </span>Any Personal Information you submit to our Platform will be subject to the terms of this Privacy Policy. The information we collect includes your name, email address, phone number, date of birth, residential address, a copy of your residential lease, a copy of your government ID, and a copy non-government ID.
            <br>
            <span class="font-bold">b. Cookies. </span>When you use the Services, Lutendi Systems Inc. may collect certain information through technologies such as cookies and other automatic data collection technologies (“Cookies”). We may use Cookies for authentication and to compile aggregate statistics about usage of the Services, such as how long Users spend using the Platform, and what parts or pages of the Website are viewed most often. This information is used to improve the content and operation of the Services. We may also use Cookies to promote the Services through marketing and advertising. These Cookies may be accessed or disclosed to third parties for the purpose of serving you relevant advertisements. You may opt out of Cookies or prevent third-party websites from accessing our Cookies by adjusting your privacy settings on your browser. However, opting out of Cookies may disable some features of the Services and may prevent us from providing you with the information and services you have requested.
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pb-5">
        <span class="font-bold">3. Information Provided to Us. </span>We may collect Personal Information disclosed to us as follows:
        <br>
        <div class="pl-10">
            <span class="font-bold">a. Third-Party Integrations. </span>We may integrate with or rely on third-party platforms and services to provide the Services to you (“Third-Party Integrations”). Any Personal Information submitted to us via Third-Party Integrations that we can access will be subject to this Privacy Policy, but please note that such Personal Information will also be subject to the terms of the applicable Third-Party Integration.
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pb-5">
        <span class="font-bold">4. How We Use Information We Collect. </span>We use Personal Information in the following ways:
        <br>
        <div class="pl-10">
            <span class="font-bold">a. </span>To authenticate and provide you access to the Services; 
